abstract: It is our accommodations, often but not exclusively technological in nature, that make it possible for many of us to do our jobs.
snippet: It is our accommodations, often but not exclusively technological in nature, that make it possible for many of us to do our jobs.
lead_paragraph: This week, John Fetterman, the Democratic nominee for the Senate from Pennsylvania, appeared in what NBC News billed as his first on-camera, one-on-one interview since he had a stroke in May. The interview went well and was conducted with Mr. Fetterman and the reporter, Dasha Burns, sitting in the same room, as Mr. Fetterman used a captioning system on a computer screen to assist him with his auditory processing, something he has needed help with since the stroke.

main: Why That John Fetterman Interview Caused a Furor
print_headline: Adapting to Disability Isn’t a Crutch. It’s the Future.

abstract: Acting tough doesn’t make you strong, even militarily.
snippet: Acting tough doesn’t make you strong, even militarily.
lead_paragraph: Credit where credit is due: Make America Great Again was a brilliant slogan, precisely because nobody knew what it meant. Was it about bringing back jobs in manufacturing? Was it about restoring straight, white, Christian men to what some of them thought was their natural position of social dominance? MAGA became all-purpose code for reversing whatever was bugging you about 21st-century America.

main: What Ukraine Teaches Us About Power

abstract: The high failure rate of the elite force’s selection course shunts hundreds of candidates into low-skilled jobs.
snippet: The high failure rate of the elite force’s selection course shunts hundreds of candidates into low-skilled jobs.
lead_paragraph: NAVAL BASE KITSAP, Wash. — A sailor fresh out of the elite Navy SEAL selection course slung his gear over his broad shoulder and clomped down a steel ladder into the guts of a Navy ship to execute a difficult, dayslong mission specifically assigned to him: scrubbing the stinking scum out of the ship’s cavernous bilge tank.

main: Recruited for Navy SEALs, Many Sailors Wind Up Scraping Paint
print_headline: From SEAL Training to a Career of Scrubbing Scum in the Bilge

abstract: Radio astronomers have captured a wide-angle image of one of the most violent locales in the cosmos.
snippet: Radio astronomers have captured a wide-angle image of one of the most violent locales in the cosmos.
lead_paragraph: A patch of pure nothing in a faraway galaxy has lately become the gravitational center of attention for radio astronomers. That would be a giant black hole, with the gravity of 6.5 billion suns, that spits high-energy particles from the center of the galaxy Messier 87, which lies some 50 million light-years from Earth.

main: A Fresh View of an Increasingly Familiar Black Hole
print_headline: A Darker View: Taking a More Expansive Look At an Ever-More-Familiar Black Hole

abstract: Let’s not make the same mistake again.
snippet: Let’s not make the same mistake again.
lead_paragraph: Is there anything liberals can do about Ron DeSantis other than quietly seethe, loudly condemn him every time he makes headlines and hope that his political flaws — his distaste for glad-handing, his less-than-inspiring public speaking style, his conspicuous unlikability — will take him down before he gets anywhere close to the presidency? It would be tempting to write off DeSantis, the bombastic Republican governor of Florida, as another unelectable right-wing lunatic unfit for national office.

main: What Liberals Can Learn From Ron DeSantis
print_headline: Liberals Can Learn Something From DeSantis

lead_paragraph: After the House passed legislation to suspend the debt ceiling and limit federal spending last night, the bill moved to the Senate for approval. Leaders of both parties in the chamber are now fending off efforts to derail its passage and deliver the bill for President Biden’s signature before a default on U.S. debt, which is set to take place on Monday.

main: Senate Leaders Race to Avert a Default

abstract: The New York City ratings were announced Thursday, with the three-star ranks unchanged.
snippet: The New York City ratings were announced Thursday, with the three-star ranks unchanged.
lead_paragraph: Michelin’s three-star rankings remained the same, but a number of New York restaurants moved off the one- and two-star lists when the Michelin Guide’s 2022 star rankings for New York were announced Thursday evening at a gala celebration at Peak in Hudson Yards in Manhattan. The top restaurants remain the same as last year: Chef’s Table at Brooklyn Fare, Eleven Madison Park, Le Bernardin, Masa and Per Se. But there were changes in other categories.

main: Peter Luger and Carbone Among Michelin Star Losers and Winners
